definition[0]: a wild open area of high land, covered with rough grass or low bushes and heather, that is not farmed because the soil is not good enough
example[0]: They went grouse shooting up on the moors.
definition[1]: to fasten a ship or boat to the land or to the bottom of the sea using ropes or an anchor
example[2]: Two or three fishing boats were moored alongside the pier.
definition[2]: one of the Muslim people from North Africa who entered Spain in the 8th century and ruled the southern part of the country until 1492
